comments: Whitmore (HOU) and Thomas (BKN) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Thomas (BKN) gathers the ball and jumps with the intent to pass when he lands before releasing the ball.
Dinwiddie (BKN) brings his off-arm toward VanVleet's (HOU) space, and marginal contact occurs as Dinwiddie releases away during the drive.
Dinwiddie (BKN) slides his hand off Green (HOU) as he aligns alongside Green's path, and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Green (HOU) goes to, not through, Dinwiddie's (BKN) space and marginal contact occurs as Green releases away during the drive.
VanVleet (HOU) moves alongside Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.

After Claxton (BKN) has already lost control of the rebound, Whitmore (HOU) swipes toward the loose ball, and marginal contact occurs with Claxton. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Claxton (BKN) and Tate (HOU) both engage and separate during the rebound.
Brooks (HOU) commits a take foul on Smith Jr. (BKN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Finney-Smith (BKN) legally contests VanVleet's (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Bridges (BKN) slides his hand off the ball and onto Sengun's (HOU) arm, affecting his layup attempt.
Thompson (HOU) initiates contact by wrapping his arm around Thomas' (BKN) upper body, which affects his FOM before the ball has been released during the inbound.
Green (HOU) makes clean contact with the ball and then he and Thomas (BKN) both have their hands firmly on it, which should have resulted in a jump ball.
Sengun (HOU) and Bridges (BKN) both engage during the off-ball screen, causing marginal contact to occur before they separate.
Bridges (BKN) extends both hands forward and commits a take foul on VanVleet (HOU) before the shot.
VanVleet (HOU) steps over the free-throw line before the shot touches the backboard.
Claxton (BKN) continues to move into Sengun's (HOU) body and impedes his ability to pursue the rebound.
Thompson (HOU) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (BKN).
